args:
The time was ten years ago. I had just graduated
from the Officers Academy and was assigned to a
team formed to deal with a bombing incident
perpetrated by an anti-monarchy organization.

It was a crime of unprecedented scale, which is
why we knights were asked to help. So I worked
around the clock alongside my former schoolmates
Harle and Cecile to bring about a resolution.

All we did, we did for the sake of peace in Alberia.
And then, at long last, we succeeded in detaining
the man we believed responsible for all of the
insurrectionist activity in New Town. But...

That's right, chum! And while you lot were
spinning your heads this way and that
trying to chase me down, my comrades set
up magical explosives all over Old Town.
The moment we want it to, the entire\nplace goes BOOOOM!
You would take all the inhabitants of Old\nTown hostage? How monstrous!

Now then, you're going to go and give the
ones who hold your leashes a message:
We demand the complete and immediate
abolition of the monarchy!
If it doesn't happen, we'll blow Old Town\nsky-high and take aaaall of your precious\nAlberian subjects with it!
Hostage-taking is bad enough, but you now\nseek the forfeiture of our beloved royal\nfamily's authority on top of it?

No, such things can wait. Cecile and Harle,
take this man to headquarters and await
instructions. I will go ahead to Old Town
and find a way to disarm the explosives.
Meet me there when you are finished.
Stop, Leif! Think about this for a moment!\nWe don't even know if you CAN disarm\nthose explosives!
There is no other option if we hope to save\nall the people of Old Town.

...I'm afraid that's impossible. With the
situation as it is, there's essentially no
chance of saving every single resident of
Old Town.
That man's deadline bears down on us.\nThere is no time to search for devices\nwhose locations are completely unknown.
And continuing to bet on those ever-\nshrinking odds smacks of hubris.
It's vexing to say this, but Harle is right.\nSometimes hard decisions must be made\nfor the sake of justice.
Believe me, I want to save these people as\nmuch as you—which is why we should\nnow apply our efforts to evacuating them.
We won't be able to save everyone, but\nwe'll be able to save some—and I think\nthat is the best outcome we can hope for.
So you're telling me to judge which lives\ntake precedence?
Of course. Does something about that\nstrike you as odd?
I hear the truth of your words, and yet I\ncannot abide the though of condemning\neven a single person to death.
So long as a hint of possibility remains,\nI refuse to give up on saving everyone.
That man could find the upside of a\ntornado. It's nauseating.
I heard there was an explosion on the\nmain street. Are you okay?
Yes. My apologies for worrying you.

Still, perhaps you can help me with
something. This bombing used a magical
explosive. It's the same sort of method
as the past incident.
Well, that's troubling. Do you think\nthey're connected somehow?
I cannot say for certain as yet. Honestly,\nI don't even have a good motive.
But the older incident was aimed at\nabolishing the monarchy. Has there\nbeen similar seditious talk here?
Not that I've heard—and I would know,\nconsidering I work at the assembly hall\nand talk to people all day long.
But if I do hear anything like that,\nI'll come to you straightaway.
Thank you. Still...hmm. Perhaps I am\ngrasping for a connection between the\nincidents when none actually exists.
But if that is the case, why in the\nGoddess's name are they DOING this?
Maybe we can think on that together.
See, 'cause I bet all of this has something\nto do with what I'm looking into.
Cecile! What are you doing here?!

Chelle asked me to handle a little
investigation for her, and this city's
assembly hall was my next stop to
gather some intelligence.
And what do I find but a familiar voice\ntalking about something very interesting.\nMind filling me in?
Of course. Here is what I know...

This is just my personal take, but I agree
that it's highly likely the explosive devices
being used here are the same type from
the previous incident.
Yes. In fact, that's what I was sent here for.
Lately, the rumor mill has been abuzz with\ntalk of magical explosives from the north\nbeing smuggled through Chanzelia.

Apparently they're the same kind as the
ones from the previous incident, and my
job is to look into it and find whoever
is responsible.
And right as I arrive here to investigate,\nboom, we get an explosion.
So I'm thinking we're after the same folks\nhere, old friend.

In that case, might I beg your aid? I could
not face my liege or the White Sparrows
again if I fail this mission—my honor as a
knight would be forever tainted.
Honor... Kniiiight... GYAAAAAH!\nI need a Manachew!
*CRUUUUNCH* Phew, okay. That's better...\nUh, I mean, I also want to see this case\nsolved! For my pride as...a mercenary.
Anyway, seeing as how one of these things\nalready went off, we'd better hurry.
There could be undetonated explosives\nat the other threatened sites.
We should check just to be sure.
...So in addition to the main street,\nthis alley has also been the target of\nnumerous threats.

Out of an abundance of caution, I had the
area evacuated. If there is anything
dangerous here, now is the time to
find and deal with it.
Nope. No familiar explosive devices, and\nnothing that even looks remotely weird.

Given that we still haven't found any
even after all this searching, maybe
the other threats were just meant
to throw us off.
Whatever the case, there's little more we\ncan do here. We should be off.
You shouldn't be here, Callan!\nIt's dangerous!
I know, and I'm sorry. It's just that you\ndidn't come back and I got worried and...\nWell, here I am, I guess.
At least eat this, all right? I'll head back\nonce you get something in your stomach.
Thank you. Cecile, you should have so—
We need to get out of here. Now!
(That's the same kind of device as before,\nand it's activated!)
(Is he frozen in place by his memories of\nthe last incident?!)
There is no choice—I have to shield him\nwith my own body!
Callan! Callan, are you all right?!
(Those burns on his legs... He must have\nlost consciousness from the pain...\nI failed to fully protect him!)
(This is just like before... The burning...\nThe faces twisted in agony...)
(They died helpless... By the Goddess,\nhave I made the same mistake again?)
Did I fail the people of Alberia again?\nIs my dream destined to wither and die?
